draw_text(info1_x, info1_y, "Russian folk songs are the living history of the Russian\npeople, dating back to the first Slavic settlers of the region.\nFolk music from Russia draws on pagan and Orthodox\nChristian traditions, focusing more on choral vocals than\ninstrumentation. Russian music often contains folk\nelements or music of other ethnic groups living in Russia,\neven in classical or military pieces. Balalaikas, domras,\nand gusli are varieties of Russian stringed instruments that\nlend folk music from this region a distinct sound.");